title: PPPP’s Naeem Kharl wins PS-30 seat
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Candidate of Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) Naeem Ahmed Kharl has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-30 Khairpur-5 constituency by securing 57,000 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Sheikh Khalid Hussain of Grand Democratic Alliance (GDA) who secured 26,913 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 39.72 per cent in the constituency.
